= class GLib::InetSocketAddress

An IPv4 or IPv6 socket address; that is, the combination of a GLib::InetAddress
and a port number. 

== Object Hierarchy

* Object
  * GLib::Instantiatable
    * GLib::Object
      * GLib::SocketAddress
        * GLib::InetSocketAddress

== Class Methods

--- GLib::InetSocketAddress.new(address, port)

     Creates a new GLib::InetSocketAddress for ((|address|)) and ((|port|)).

     * Returns: A new GLib::InetSocketAddress

== Instance Methods

--- address

    Gets the address.

     * Returns: The GLib::InetAddress

--- each

    See GLib::SocketConnectable#each.

--- enumerate

    See GLib::SocketConnectable#enumerate.

--- port

    Gets the port.

     * Returns: The port

== Properties

--- address: GLib::InetAddress (Read/Write)

    The address

--- port: Integer (Read/Write)

    The port

